00:32:13.000 --> 00:32:14.999
He's good.

00:32:15.000 --> 00:32:16.999
Hamin really is good at it.

00:32:17.000 --> 00:32:19.999
Wow.

00:32:20.000 --> 00:32:20.999
What? What is it?

00:32:21.000 --> 00:32:21.999
Our background just...

00:32:22.000 --> 00:32:23.999
Did something go wrong?

00:32:24.000 --> 00:32:25.999
Look over there in the background.

00:32:26.000 --> 00:32:27.999
There are four slices of watermelon.

00:32:28.000 --> 00:32:28.999
Who am I sharing them with?

00:32:29.000 --> 00:32:29.999
This is where the music should start.

00:32:30.000 --> 00:32:30.999
Yes.

00:32:31.000 --> 00:32:33.999
[They imitate a jingle]

00:32:34.000 --> 00:32:35.999
[The jingle continues]

00:32:36.000 --> 00:32:37.999
Another fun day at Noah's place.

00:32:38.000 --> 00:32:40.999
Today, Bamby is visiting.

00:32:41.000 --> 00:32:43.999
Now, the onggi jars over there...
have kimchi stew inside.

00:32:44.000 --> 00:32:44.999
Kimchi stew?

00:32:45.000 --> 00:32:45.999
Inside those jars.

00:32:46.000 --> 00:32:46.999
Of course.

00:32:47.000 --> 00:32:47.999
Not gochujang or doenjang...

00:32:48.000 --> 00:32:48.999
but kimchi stew.

00:32:49.000 --> 00:32:49.999
There's kimchi stew inside?

00:32:50.000 --> 00:32:50.999
Of course.

00:32:51.000 --> 00:32:51.999
Are you aging it in there?

00:32:52.000 --> 00:32:52.999
You mean kimchi-jjim?

00:32:53.000 --> 00:32:55.999
Yes.

00:32:56.000 --> 00:32:56.999
[Panting]

00:32:57.000 --> 00:32:59.999
The kimchi-jjim is really in there?

00:33:00.000 --> 00:33:03.999
[Laughs] Yes. Okay.

00:33:04.000 --> 00:33:04.999
I said it is.

00:33:05.000 --> 00:33:05.999
Okay.

00:33:06.000 --> 00:33:07.999
Moving on...

00:33:08.000 --> 00:33:09.999
Good.

00:33:10.000 --> 00:33:11.999
Okay.

00:33:12.000 --> 00:33:12.999
[Sighs]

00:33:13.000 --> 00:33:15.999
‘Noah and Bamby, I watched the birthday stream.’

00:33:16.000 --> 00:33:18.999
They're asking about ‘Suki Sugite Metsu!’

00:33:19.000 --> 00:33:19.999
How did you make it?

00:33:20.000 --> 00:33:21.999
‘Suki Sugite Metsu!’

00:33:22.000 --> 00:33:23.999
They seem very curious...

00:33:24.000 --> 00:33:24.999
about the behind-the-scenes story.

00:33:25.000 --> 00:33:25.999
Of course.

00:33:26.000 --> 00:33:28.999
But I think the other three...

00:33:29.000 --> 00:33:30.999
already talked about it quite a lot.

00:33:31.000 --> 00:33:32.999
Do you know how much they revealed?

00:33:33.000 --> 00:33:33.999
Of course.

00:33:34.000 --> 00:33:34.999
You know?

00:33:35.000 --> 00:33:35.999
What did they say?

00:33:36.000 --> 00:33:36.999
How much did they reveal?

00:33:37.000 --> 00:33:38.999
Of course. Didn't you watch their stream?

00:33:39.000 --> 00:33:39.999
You know I didn't watch it.

00:33:40.000 --> 00:33:41.999
Why not?

00:33:42.000 --> 00:33:43.999
I barely saw any of it. [Laughs]

00:33:44.000 --> 00:33:45.999
What? I thought you'd watched it.

00:33:46.000 --> 00:33:47.999
You kept acting like you had.

00:33:48.000 --> 00:33:48.999
So what did they say?

00:33:49.000 --> 00:33:51.999
Well...

00:33:52.000 --> 00:33:53.999
What was it again?

00:33:54.000 --> 00:33:55.999
Why pretend if you didn't watch it?

00:33:56.000 --> 00:33:58.999
They talked about the rap part...

00:33:59.000 --> 00:34:01.999
and how an unfamiliar voice suddenly appeared.

00:34:02.000 --> 00:34:03.999
They explained all of that.

00:34:04.000 --> 00:34:06.999
They also discussed the acting scenes.

00:34:07.000 --> 00:34:07.999
They watched everything...

00:34:08.000 --> 00:34:08.999
and talked about all of it.

00:34:09.000 --> 00:34:10.999
You saw them discuss that?

00:34:11.000 --> 00:34:12.999
Yes. I even did a Weverse Live about it.

00:34:13.000 --> 00:34:13.999
Because of that.

00:34:14.000 --> 00:34:16.999
Really? Yes.

00:34:17.000 --> 00:34:17.999
Okay.

00:34:18.000 --> 00:34:19.999
Then what haven't we told them?

00:34:20.000 --> 00:34:20.999
What behind-the-scenes story is left?

00:34:21.000 --> 00:34:21.999
Hmm.

00:34:22.000 --> 00:34:24.999
Something we haven't discussed...

00:34:25.000 --> 00:34:25.999
Let's see.

00:34:26.000 --> 00:34:28.999
For this cover...

00:34:29.000 --> 00:34:30.999
everything moved rather urgently.

00:34:31.000 --> 00:34:33.999
If we'd formally booked our recording studio...

00:34:34.000 --> 00:34:35.999
brought in the engineer...

00:34:36.000 --> 00:34:38.999
and had a Japanese pronunciation coach there...

00:34:39.000 --> 00:34:39.999
Yes.

00:34:40.000 --> 00:34:40.999
Right.

00:34:41.000 --> 00:34:42.999
the recording would have taken far too long.

00:34:43.000 --> 00:34:43.999
That's what I thought.

00:34:44.000 --> 00:34:44.999
Especially because it was Japanese.

00:34:45.000 --> 00:34:45.999
Yes.

00:34:46.000 --> 00:34:46.999
So...

00:34:47.000 --> 00:34:49.999
I knew my heart would start racing...

00:34:50.000 --> 00:34:51.999
if it dragged on.

00:34:52.000 --> 00:34:53.999
I decided we had to move quickly.

00:34:54.000 --> 00:34:55.999
Because it naturally could have taken ages.

00:34:56.000 --> 00:34:57.999
Right.

00:34:58.000 --> 00:34:59.999
So I thought...

00:35:00.000 --> 00:35:01.999
it would be better if I handled it quickly.

00:35:02.000 --> 00:35:02.999
Right, right.

00:35:03.000 --> 00:35:04.999
I said I'd take charge.

00:35:05.000 --> 00:35:05.999
Then I brought them in one by one.

00:35:06.000 --> 00:35:07.999
I sat down...

00:35:08.000 --> 00:35:08.999
placed each member right beside me...

00:35:09.000 --> 00:35:09.999
and we really did move quickly.

00:35:10.000 --> 00:35:11.999
We recorded one person at a time.

00:35:12.000 --> 00:35:13.999
I took all the short lines...

00:35:14.000 --> 00:35:14.999
and assembled them rapidly.

00:35:15.000 --> 00:35:15.999
Right.

00:35:16.000 --> 00:35:17.999
Then, after each line was sung...

00:35:18.000 --> 00:35:18.999
we finished assembling it...

00:35:19.000 --> 00:35:19.999
and asked, ‘How is the pronunciation?’

00:35:20.000 --> 00:35:20.999
Right. ‘This part isn't good.’ Okay...

00:35:21.000 --> 00:35:22.999
then record it again.

00:35:23.000 --> 00:35:24.999
We put it together like Lego pieces...

00:35:25.000 --> 00:35:26.999
and finished quite quickly.

00:35:27.000 --> 00:35:27.999
Yes.

00:35:28.000 --> 00:35:28.999
And then...

00:35:29.000 --> 00:35:30.999
especially the rap.

00:35:31.000 --> 00:35:31.999
The rap...

00:35:32.000 --> 00:35:33.999
featured a very unfamiliar voice.

00:35:34.000 --> 00:35:35.999
But honestly...

00:35:36.000 --> 00:35:37.999
this is how I see it.

00:35:38.000 --> 00:35:38.999
When you make a cover song...

00:35:39.000 --> 00:35:39.999
Yes.

00:35:40.000 --> 00:35:42.999
if you sing it exactly like the original artist...

00:35:43.000 --> 00:35:46.999
with exactly the same vocal color...

00:35:47.000 --> 00:35:48.999
and imitate everything perfectly...

00:35:49.000 --> 00:35:51.999
why not simply listen to the original?

00:35:52.000 --> 00:35:53.999
That's what I think.

00:35:54.000 --> 00:35:56.999
If you're going to make a cover...

00:35:57.000 --> 00:35:57.999
it needn’t be a full reinterpretation...

00:35:58.000 --> 00:35:59.999
but it should contain...

00:36:00.000 --> 00:36:01.999
some of PLAVE's own character.

00:36:02.000 --> 00:36:02.999
I felt we needed that special point.

00:36:03.000 --> 00:36:04.999
Something distinctive.

00:36:05.000 --> 00:36:07.999
But the members kept saying...

00:36:08.000 --> 00:36:09.999
‘This doesn't sound like my voice.’

00:36:10.000 --> 00:36:10.999
They were worried about that.

00:36:11.000 --> 00:36:12.999
I told them no.

00:36:13.000 --> 00:36:13.999
‘That's the killer detail.’

00:36:14.000 --> 00:36:16.999
I think the rap part...

00:36:17.000 --> 00:36:18.999
is the cover's biggest highlight.

00:36:19.000 --> 00:36:20.999
Looking at the whole thing...

00:36:21.000 --> 00:36:22.999
I desperately wanted to record mine again.

00:36:23.000 --> 00:36:23.999
Yes.

00:36:24.000 --> 00:36:25.999
I think I sang it once or twice.

00:36:26.000 --> 00:36:26.999
Maybe only once.

00:36:27.000 --> 00:36:28.999
Right. You said, ‘This is enough.’

00:36:29.000 --> 00:36:30.999
No. If I remember correctly...

00:36:31.000 --> 00:36:31.999
I didn't use your second take.

00:36:32.000 --> 00:36:33.999
I think I used the entire first take.

00:36:34.000 --> 00:36:34.999
That's why I thought it made no sense.

00:36:35.000 --> 00:36:37.999
Even as we were leaving...

00:36:38.000 --> 00:36:39.999
and recording other parts...

00:36:40.000 --> 00:36:41.999
you kept asking to record it again.

00:36:42.000 --> 00:36:44.999
I told you, ‘Go home. It's done.’ [Laughs]

00:36:45.000 --> 00:36:45.999
That really happened.

00:36:46.000 --> 00:36:48.999
But it came out well...

00:36:49.000 --> 00:36:50.999
and the fans loved it.
That's what surprised me.

00:36:51.000 --> 00:36:51.999
From now on, trust me.

00:36:52.000 --> 00:36:53.999
Now that hyung’s instincts were proven right...

00:36:54.000 --> 00:36:55.999
you can say things like that.

00:36:56.000 --> 00:36:56.999
Understood. Do you understand now? Yes.

00:36:57.000 --> 00:36:58.999
So that was another behind-the-scenes story.

00:36:59.000 --> 00:36:59.999
And also...

00:37:00.000 --> 00:37:00.999
during filming...

00:37:01.000 --> 00:37:02.999
During filming...

00:37:03.000 --> 00:37:04.999
we tried very hard to look genuinely excited.

00:37:05.000 --> 00:37:05.999
We really did.

00:37:06.000 --> 00:37:06.999
Right.

00:37:07.000 --> 00:37:08.999
We wanted to truly enjoy the song.

00:37:09.000 --> 00:37:11.999
That was our mindset with the original.

00:37:12.000 --> 00:37:13.999
So I danced much bigger...

00:37:14.000 --> 00:37:15.999
and exaggerated every movement.

00:37:16.000 --> 00:37:16.999
Right.

00:37:17.000 --> 00:37:17.999
People really liked that.

00:37:18.000 --> 00:37:19.999
Yes. And this part...

00:37:20.000 --> 00:37:20.999
was almost a full burpee.

00:37:21.000 --> 00:37:22.999
Yes. Seriously.

00:37:23.000 --> 00:37:24.999
I deliberately made everything bigger...

00:37:25.000 --> 00:37:26.999
and gave it everything I had.

00:37:27.000 --> 00:37:29.999
It felt like my body was breaking.

00:37:30.000 --> 00:37:31.999
Ah...

00:37:32.000 --> 00:37:32.999
Anyway, that happened.

00:37:33.000 --> 00:37:33.999
That's the story.

00:37:34.000 --> 00:37:35.999
It was a very fun project.

00:37:36.000 --> 00:37:38.999
Yes, it was fun.

00:37:39.000 --> 00:37:40.999
We worked very hard on it...

00:37:41.000 --> 00:37:41.999
and the response was wonderful.

00:37:42.000 --> 00:37:43.999
That makes us so happy.

00:37:44.000 --> 00:37:45.999
Thank you for enjoying it, everyone.

00:37:46.000 --> 00:37:46.999
Thank you so much.

00:37:47.000 --> 00:37:49.999
Truly.

00:37:50.000 --> 00:37:51.999
Now that we've talked about that...

00:37:52.000 --> 00:37:53.999
I'm the MC today.

00:37:54.000 --> 00:37:54.999
So I'll lead the show, understood?

00:37:55.000 --> 00:37:56.999
All right?

00:37:57.000 --> 00:37:58.999
Hyung and I, compared with our debut days...

00:37:59.000 --> 00:38:00.999
you and I have become much closer.

00:38:01.000 --> 00:38:01.999
Become what? Closer.

00:38:02.000 --> 00:38:02.999
Okay.

00:38:03.000 --> 00:38:05.999
Yes, much closer.

00:38:06.000 --> 00:38:07.999
In The Little Prince...

00:38:08.000 --> 00:38:09.999
they call that being tamed.

00:38:10.000 --> 00:38:10.999
I think you've been tamed by me.

00:38:11.000 --> 00:38:11.999
Ah.

00:38:12.000 --> 00:38:14.999
So that's why I'm the fox today.

00:38:15.000 --> 00:38:18.999
You didn't know? No, I didn't.

00:38:19.000 --> 00:38:20.999
I was wondering why today...

00:38:21.000 --> 00:38:22.999
I kept wondering, ‘Why am I the fox?’

00:38:23.000 --> 00:38:24.999
That's what I was thinking.

00:38:25.000 --> 00:38:25.999
Seriously?

00:38:26.000 --> 00:38:26.999
The Little Prince.

00:38:27.000 --> 00:38:28.999
Oh, so that's why I'm the fox.

00:38:29.000 --> 00:38:29.999
The pieces finally fit, don't they?

00:38:30.000 --> 00:38:31.999
Now the puzzle makes sense.

00:38:32.000 --> 00:38:32.999
This is the greatest plot twist.

00:38:33.000 --> 00:38:35.999
So that's what it was.

00:38:36.000 --> 00:38:37.999
The ultimate suspense.

00:38:38.000 --> 00:38:38.999
[Snorts]

00:38:39.000 --> 00:38:40.999
Even while reading the script...

00:38:41.000 --> 00:38:42.999
I couldn't understand why it said ‘tamed.’

00:38:43.000 --> 00:38:44.999
The Little Prince and the fox—you know.

00:38:45.000 --> 00:38:46.999
Yes.

00:38:47.000 --> 00:38:47.999
Isn't that the story?

00:38:48.000 --> 00:38:48.999
The one where he raises it?

00:38:49.000 --> 00:38:49.999
Right. That's the one.

00:38:50.000 --> 00:38:50.999
Exactly.

00:38:51.000 --> 00:38:52.999
I didn't realize. I did read it...

00:38:53.000 --> 00:38:55.999
but it was so long ago.

00:38:56.000 --> 00:38:56.999
Now you finally know.

00:38:57.000 --> 00:38:57.999
I understand now.

00:38:58.000 --> 00:38:59.999
Nearly 37 minutes into the stream...

00:39:00.000 --> 00:39:02.999
Noah is finally discovering...

00:39:03.000 --> 00:39:03.999
what today's concept is.

00:39:04.000 --> 00:39:05.999
Meanwhile, our Bamby...

00:39:06.000 --> 00:39:08.999
is so quick and accurate.

00:39:09.000 --> 00:39:11.999
Impressive as always.

00:39:12.000 --> 00:39:13.999
Ah, we did well with this.

00:39:14.000 --> 00:39:16.999
Now I understand, hyung.

00:39:17.000 --> 00:39:18.999
You're my pet—the cute pet.

00:39:19.000 --> 00:39:21.999
Okay, okay.

00:39:22.000 --> 00:39:23.999
[Sighs] Now that we've come this far...

00:39:24.000 --> 00:39:27.999
we can't simply claim we've been tamed.

00:39:28.000 --> 00:39:29.999
That wouldn't prove anything.

00:39:30.000 --> 00:39:30.999
Let’s test how well we know each other.

00:39:31.000 --> 00:39:32.999
how well Noah-hyung and I know each other.

00:39:33.000 --> 00:39:33.999
We'll find out.

00:39:34.000 --> 00:39:35.999
How will we test it?

00:39:36.000 --> 00:39:37.999
How about singing a song?

00:39:38.000 --> 00:39:38.999
Can singing prove that?

00:39:39.000 --> 00:39:40.999
No, it can't.

00:39:41.000 --> 00:39:42.999
It just fits the flow of the show.

00:39:43.000 --> 00:39:45.999
Oh, just for the transition. Okay.

00:39:46.000 --> 00:39:48.999
Then we'll need microphones.

00:39:49.000 --> 00:39:50.999
We'd appreciate some microphones.

00:39:51.000 --> 00:39:55.999
Here they come—yap!

00:39:56.000 --> 00:39:57.999
Okay.

00:39:58.000 --> 00:39:59.999
May I warm up my voice first?

00:40:00.000 --> 00:40:00.999
May I?

00:40:01.000 --> 00:40:04.999
I just went straight into it. [Laughs]

00:40:05.000 --> 00:40:06.999
[Clears throat]

00:40:07.000 --> 00:40:09.999
Ah... ha...

00:40:10.000 --> 00:40:25.999
[Vocal warm-up]

00:40:26.000 --> 00:40:26.999
[Groans]

00:40:27.000 --> 00:40:32.999
[Noah sings a playful line]

00:40:33.000 --> 00:40:42.999
They say Bonggu is doing a good job hosting.

00:40:43.000 --> 00:40:50.999
[Singing]

00:40:51.000 --> 00:40:53.999
[Singing]

00:40:54.000 --> 00:40:59.999
[Vocal warm-up]

00:41:00.000 --> 00:41:00.999
[Playful crying]

00:41:01.000 --> 00:41:03.999
Ah.

00:41:04.000 --> 00:41:09.999
Amazing.

00:41:10.000 --> 00:41:11.999
[Snorts]

00:41:12.000 --> 00:41:14.999
Wow, I...

00:41:15.000 --> 00:41:15.999
I said I was eating it.

00:41:16.000 --> 00:41:16.999
What? I don't know.

00:41:17.000 --> 00:41:19.999
Seriously.

00:41:20.000 --> 00:41:21.999
Taking Yonggaksan really does something.

00:41:22.000 --> 00:41:22.999
What does it do?

00:41:23.000 --> 00:41:24.999
First, there's the placebo effect.

00:41:25.000 --> 00:41:26.999
Ah. [Laughs]

00:41:27.000 --> 00:41:28.999
It gives you a sense of reassurance.

00:41:29.000 --> 00:41:30.999
So it has that effect. But actually...

00:41:31.000 --> 00:41:32.999
it does settle your throat a little.

00:41:33.000 --> 00:41:37.999
What was that? You startled me.

00:41:38.000 --> 00:41:41.999
My hand was already over here.

00:41:42.000 --> 00:41:43.999
Mm-hm.

00:41:44.000 --> 00:41:44.999
Ah.

00:41:45.000 --> 00:41:46.999
What song should we sing?

00:41:47.000 --> 00:41:49.999
[Sighs] PLLI keeps suggesting songs.

00:41:50.000 --> 00:41:50.999
PLLI?

00:41:51.000 --> 00:41:51.999
Yes, PLLI.

00:41:52.000 --> 00:41:52.999
Looking at their suggestions...

00:41:53.000 --> 00:41:57.999
there are a lot.

00:41:58.000 --> 00:42:00.999
They're asking for ‘Manchan-ga’...

00:42:01.000 --> 00:42:02.999
and ‘My Heart.’

00:42:03.000 --> 00:42:03.999
What else?

00:42:04.000 --> 00:42:05.999
They want ‘My Heart.’

00:42:06.000 --> 00:42:06.999
They're asking for Yonggaksan?

00:42:07.000 --> 00:42:08.999
Yes, Yonggaksan. What else?

00:42:09.000 --> 00:42:10.999
Anything?

00:42:11.000 --> 00:42:12.999
Ah.

00:42:13.000 --> 00:42:14.999
There are several other requests too.

00:42:15.000 --> 00:42:17.999
All kinds of songs.

00:42:18.000 --> 00:42:19.999
Sorry, Little Prince.

00:42:20.000 --> 00:42:22.999
That isn't what we prepared today.

00:42:23.000 --> 00:42:23.999
[Clears throat] ‘Love Rain.’

00:42:24.000 --> 00:42:26.999
‘Love Rain’?

00:42:27.000 --> 00:42:29.999
Ah.

00:42:30.000 --> 00:42:33.999
Aha.

00:42:34.000 --> 00:42:42.999
Na-ha...

00:42:43.000 --> 00:42:44.999
Let's try it. Are you ready?

00:42:45.000 --> 00:42:49.999
Yes, let's go. Okay. [Clears throat]

00:42:50.000 --> 00:42:50.999
Please turn the backing track up...

00:42:51.000 --> 00:42:55.999
like before.

00:42:56.000 --> 00:43:08.999
Please start it.

00:43:09.000 --> 00:43:13.999
[Music]

00:43:14.000 --> 00:43:14.999
[Music]

00:43:15.000 --> 00:43:18.999
[They prepare to sing]

00:43:19.000 --> 00:43:21.999
[Music]

00:43:22.000 --> 00:43:24.999
[Noah and Bamby sing ‘Love Rain’]

00:43:25.000 --> 00:43:28.999
[Music]

00:43:29.000 --> 00:43:33.999
[They sing]

00:43:34.000 --> 00:43:37.999
[Music]

